headline: For Dow Banking Giant Goldman Sachs, A 'Trump Bump' Seems Likely
summary: Goldman Sachs is Monday's IBD Stock Of The Day as the Dow and S&P 500 banking stock eyes a buy point just above a key trading level amid its 55% advance this year.  Morgan Stanley analyst Betsy Graseck on Monday upped the price target on Goldman Sachs shares to 736, up from 570.  For the full year, the consensus puts Goldman Sachs profit up 60% to $36.63 per share on sales totaling $51.71 billion, a 12% gain compared with 2023.
